<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#F0DCA0">Originally posted by Alrik Fassbauer on 01-11-2000 06:25 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=20 COLS=75 WRAP="VIRTUAL">Indeed, I'm not a dwarf.
I'm just physically relatively small (1.68 or 1.65 meters).
But I would't have anything against using my name. I'd just be glad the name ist in the game, however.  ;)
Someone who owns a copy of the english version of the old DSA-games (you know, Blade of destiny, Startrail, Shadows over Rive [I don't know whether these ara EXACTLY the names of the english versions...) should have a translation of the "Streuner", because that's one of the Characters playable in the game. At least in the german version.

I'd prefer  names like the Hilmar Haudrauf (What's the translation ?) and Amboß (kind of a blacksmith or so), names that actually appeared in the forums (the Amboß appeared in the LMK-Forum).

Sounding names: Something that sounds like stones, however, just because dwarfes normally have to to with stones (Digging In The Dirt, Peter Gabriel, Ex-Genesis).
Or something that sounds like, hm, war or so, because dwarfs typically are well-armoured and ideal war-fighters. As far as I know (one can never be sure whether there might be an single individual which does NOT conform with the cliches).


------------------
MFG (Mehr Fürs Geld), Alrik. 
</TEXTAREA>
